:: Significance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Following Fox&rsquo;s transformation and the revelation of new aspects of his identity, his relationship to both Nuna and sila changes along with his new form. Moreover, Fox&rsquo;s metamorphosis acts as a lens that <em>reveals </em>new aspects of the landscape and teaches the player new ways of seeing and interacting with familiar space. The scene immediately following Fox&rsquo;s transformation most closely mimics the opening scenes of the game in its brightness, color, and ease of mechanics:
<br /><strong>(Insert thumbnails comparing different parts of the game here - </strong>beginning, water level, night level, underground, post-transformation<strong>)</strong>
<br />From a strictly visual standpoint, this scene marks a return to the start of the game - Fox&rsquo;s ending turned beginning again. However, in addition to Fox&rsquo;s new form, there is one key difference. For the first time in the game, sila is attached to a corporeal physical form: the trees. Suddenly, sila is more than an abstraction floating ephemerally in space that (to a casual observer) is empty. Sila is revealed to be an aspect of things that are concrete and tangible - a particular way of perceiving meaning, of seeing layers of knowledge and liveliness that go beyond physical sight (a conceptualization that dovetails with Martin&rsquo;s definition of sila as &ldquo;wisdom&rdquo;). Just as Fox, who once appeared to be a regular fox, is revealed to have multiple layers of form and spirit in the form of different skins, so too sila reveals a new &ldquo;skin&rdquo; of physicality in the form of the trees. The player&rsquo;s ability to see this new form of sila is directly linked to the revelation of Fox&rsquo;s new form, as the narration and subtitles confirm: &ldquo;floating high above the forest floor, fox continued to reveal the beauty of the helping spirits.&rdquo; The verbal affirmation that Fox is revealing sila to Nuna (and to the players) serves as another echo to the beginning of the game, when Fox&rsquo;s communication with sila was acknowledged and formally framed in a similar way.<a title="" href="#_ftn1" name="_ftnref1">[1]</a> In this way, Fox&rsquo;s new skin opens a scene that re-iterates the expository nature of the game&rsquo;s beginning through the lens of Fox&rsquo;s new form.
